Esser proposes to equate to extremism the insult of patriotic feelings
For the legislative protection of patriotic feelings of citizens from provocations and insults directed against Russia, Fair Russia proposes to equate the insult of patriotic feelings to extremist activity and to punish for this for five years in prison.
According to the newspaper Izvestia, such amendments to the legislation, prepared by the Deputy Chairman of the Duma Committee on Energy Oleg Mikheev, have already been sent to the Supreme Court and the government to obtain an opinion.
Under the patriotic feelings of citizens, the author of the amendments proposes to understand the emotional connection of a person with the country of which he is a citizen, characterized by love for that country, responsible attitude to its fate, respect for its history and culture.
As Mikheev points out, in domestic legislation there are sanctions for abuse of formal signs of state power - the flag and the coat of arms.
At the same time, according to the parliamentarian, the protection of Russians, whose feelings may be affected by the insult of state symbols, and other manifestations of disrespect for our country, has not been worked out enough in Russian legislation.
As an example, he cites the annual Victory Day debates, when some media persons allow themselves to question the heroic feat of the people of the USSR in the fight against the fascists.
On the eve of the main national holiday - Victory Day on May 9 - annually unfolds a real wakhanalia.
Exercising in wit and an “alternative view” of history, some publicists come to the argument that, to say, how sad that the cultural Germans did not conquer the wild Soviet Union!
I consider this absolutely unacceptable in a country where pride in history remains the main "spiritual stronghold" of the nation," - outraged Oleg Mikheev.
In addition, according to Mikheev, patriotically-minded people in Russia are much more than religious, but the law punishes for insulting the feelings of believers, and to insult patriotic feelings can be almost without punishment.
In the opinion of the elected representative, it is necessary to equate the insult of patriotic feelings with extremist activity and to prescribe in article 282 of the Criminal Code the corresponding punishment.
The bill provides for punishment for insulting patriotic feelings: from a 100,000 fine to a 5-year prison sentence.
