“The law gives parents time not to make hasty decisions themselves,” Barac said.
It gives them time to do some analysis and understand the situation, as well as the time interval before they write “male” or “female.”
In this case, you're fine - raise a child, love the child.
You have a wonderful child, and you feel joy.
We don't have to rush into an operation that's irreversible.
“It allows children to participate in decision-making and eliminates the anxiety that drives parents because they don’t feel they are doing the right thing,” she said.
