Energetics of Dnipropetrovsk began a unique program to save... nest of aistov
In ancient times, to bring to the courtyard of the Aistos, peasants on a high column installed a wheel from the cart, and a heavy nest well held on it.
Such special supports have not been put for a long time, so the aist loved the pillars of the power lines - the intertwined branches rely on wires, thanks to which the real house stands reliably.
Grandmother Anya, near whose house in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district has been living a real family for twenty years, began to notice how the nest settles, despite all the efforts of its inhabitants.
Birds put new vents on top, and the bottom layer has already slid between the wires, is about to collapse.
Of course, it is a pity that the family of Aistos, who every year nested at the yard, brought out and fed three or four birds during the summer, but also do not want to be without light.
As soon as the birds flew to the warm lands, grandmother Anya called Tsarichansky RES, which owns the support.
I didn’t expect them to react so quickly.
When our specialists came to Ivanovka, they were surprised that the nest is still held at all, - said the technical director of DTEK "Dneprooblenergo" Sergei Berezovsky.
On the wires, which turned out to be, in fact, already inside the nest, weighing 150 - 200 kilograms, began corrosion.
At any moment, the birds could die from electric discharge.
And local residents risked being left out of the light due to damage to the wires.
Therefore, linear monitors began the operation to save the nest, and this is not the first time in our practice.
Helped scientists-ornithologists from the Dnipropetrovsk National University, who developed a scheme for the transfer of the nest.
They also conducted trainings for employees of the district networks.
The famous Dnepropetrovsk ornithologist Alexander Ponomarenko advised energy engineers at all stages of the reconstruction of the nests.
To begin with, it was calculated that there are more than 50 real "apartments" in the area in an emergency state.
For their reconstruction, special metal platforms resembling a funnel were welded.
The base was strewn with branches, and then the old nest was moved there.
According to experts, it is enough to lay the old branches as a basis for the birds to recognize the nest and return to it.
After that, the owners will build their own house.
A month ago, the first nest was reconstructed in the village of Peschanka Novomoskovsky district.
A new reinforced concrete pillar was placed next to the electric pole and a platform with an old, already inhabited nest was placed on it.
The entire operation cost the energy companies nine thousand hryvnias.
And the other day the same new settlement took place in the village of Ivanovka Petrikovsky district in the yard of grandmother Ani.
Here the platform was fixed in the previous place, only raised above the wires.
Ornithologists are sure that cautious, conservative birds will not even notice in the spring that their "apartment" has been overhauled.
Until the end of the year, the same reconstruction awaits four more nests in Pokrovsky and Tsarichansky regions of the Dnipropetrovsk region.
By the way, while some save rare birds, others mercilessly kill them.
The other day, the whole area was covered with sad news - in the village of Ust-Kamenka in the Apostolovsky district, on the day of the opening of the pheasant hunt, poachers shot the swan family, who lived on the local pond for entertainment.
Noble birds were not afraid of people at all - the locals fed them and did not offend them.
When the villagers heard the shots, they ran to the pond, and the four beautiful swans were already lying dead on the water.
Now the employees of the Apostolic District Police Department are figuring out who shot the birds recorded in the Red Book.
The Russian march is becoming more popular.
On the 4th of November, on the Day of National Unity, an agreed with the city hall "Russian March" will be held in Moscow.
According to a survey of the Levada Center, support for the Russian Marches is growing - already 40% of citizens to varying degrees approve of the idea of holding them.
According to the Levada Center, 40% of citizens to varying degrees approve of the Russian marches: 11% of them are definitely positive and 29% - "rather positive".
The popularity of the idea of "Russian marches" is gradually growing - in 2006 these actions welcomed only 14% of Russians, and in December 2010 the holding of such events supported already twice as many citizens (28%).
"Definitely negative" to the "Russian marches" are only 7% of Russians, "rather negative" - 19%.
Another 35% could not formulate their attitude to this action.
This year, the Moscow City Hall agreed to hold a “Russian March” of up to 15,000 people in Lublin, the head of the security department of the capital Alexei Mayorov said today.
This action of nationalists has been held every year on the Day of National Unity since 2005.
To the question of sociologists "Have you heard that on November 4 in Russia are held "Russian marches" under the slogans of protection of the rights of Russians in Russia?" three-quarters (75%) of citizens responded negatively.
Only one in five Russians knows about this action (20%).
It is noteworthy that in December 2010 almost a third of citizens (31%) heard about the “Russian Marches”.
Recall that three years ago, on December 11, a spontaneous rally of nationalists took place in Manege Square, which grew into mass riots.
The Levada Center also asked the Russians about what holiday is celebrated on November 4.
In two years, the number of those who know the right answer (Day of Popular Unity) has increased from 41% to 49%.
However, only 15% of citizens are going to celebrate this holiday.
About the same amount (17%) intend to celebrate the 7th of November Day of the October Revolution.
The majority of citizens (62%) are not going to celebrate any of these holidays.
How the Moscow City Hall agreed the “Russian March” in Lublin
On October 28, the capital authorities agreed to hold the “Russian March” on November 4 in Lublin.
This was reported by the leader of the Russian Association, the organizer of the march Dmitry Demushkin.
In addition to the march in Lublin on the Day of People's Unity, a rally and rock concert of the group "Colour", also agreed with the authorities, will be held.
How was the "Russian March 2012"
On the Day of National Unity in 2012, nationalists marched from Yakimanskaya embankment to the Central House of the artist, where the rally took place.
The organizers estimated the number of participants at 20 thousand people, the Ministry of Internal Affairs called the figure 6 thousand.
Report: Obama's campaign staff considered Biden's exclusion in favor of Hillary Clinton
According to The New York Times, President Barack Obama’s closest advisers were secretly considering replacing Vice President Joe Biden with Hillary Clinton’s candidacy in the 2012 election.
This discovery is the most vivid sensation of all the expected book by Mark Galperin and John Heilemann about the 2012 campaign "The stakes are doubled: the game changed in 2012".
The Times received a copy of the forthcoming book and reported on Thursday evening that the president’s closest aides had conducted “large-scale focus group research and public opinion polls in late 2011” to assess whether Biden’s exclusion could help raise fading hopes of re-election.
According to political commentator The Times Jonathan Martin, the book gives a detailed description of the attempt of high-ranking officials of the election headquarters and the White House, namely the former head of the White House administration Bill Daley, to assess what effect the appointment of the former vice president will have on the vote.
The possible replacement was a secret, carefully guarded in the Chicago election headquarters and in the Oval Office.
Only six of the president’s closest advisers — including Daley, former Obama campaign chief Jim Messina, and former White House senior advisers David Axelrod and David Pluff — knew the replacement was under consideration.
The book "The stakes are doubled" claims that Daley was the initiator of an attempt to replace Biden despite their "close personal relationship", but ultimately declined this step when their data showed that adding Clinton to the electoral list would not "significantly improve Obama's chances".
In an interview with Martin Daley confirmed that the administration was indeed considering replacing Biden Clinton.
“I was actively advocating for a lot of things, and that was one of them,” Daley told the newspaper.
You have to remember that the president was in terrible shape at the time, so we thought, “Oh my God, what are we going to do?”
Although Daley described the study as a “necessary check,” Martin told CNN’s Anderson Cooper that the election staff had invested enough in studying whether this step would bring dividends to the vote.
“The pre-election headquarters don’t spend that kind of money on polls and focus groups unless they’re serious about something,” Martin said in the AK 360 program.
It is unclear, however, whether Obama knew that his team was exploring the possibility of a replacement.
Martin told CNN that he asked Daley if his then-boss knew about a possible reshuffle.
Although Daley said he didn’t think the president was “aware” of a possible replacement, the former head of the administration admitted that, “maybe,” Obama knew.
Martin added that the “doubled rates” does not give a clear answer to the question of whether the results of the political probe came to the Obama table.
Cooper asked Martin if he was serious about whether Obama was aware of an investigation into whether Biden could be removed from the electoral roll.
“Perhaps,” Martin replied.
