In accordance with the new guidelines, airlines whose aircraft are adequately protected from electronic interference may allow passengers to use these devices during take-off, landing and driving, FAU said.
Most new airliners and other aircraft modified so that passengers could use Wi-Fi at high altitudes are expected to meet these criteria.
