Thus, there are still no “Words with Friends” — an intelligent online game that actor Alec Baldwin played on his smartphone in 2011, when there was a notorious case: the actor was removed from an American Airlines plane for refusing to turn off the device at the time the plane landed.
And heavier devices, such as laptops, will still need to be stored in the luggage compartment, as they can injure someone if they fly around the cabin.
